This caption cleverly bridges birdwatching and music performance through wordplay. In ornithology, birdwatchers typically identify bird species by their distinctive songs or calls—a natural "song" is a biological identifier. It gently mocks both serious birdwatching conventions and transforms the scientific practice of bird identification into a music criticism scenario, creating an unexpected and humorous collision of two different worlds.
